hopobject.body: Would you like a receipt? wolfespharmacy.com However, royal items can fall and rise in line with their popularity. Mr Westwood-Brookes said: "Just after Diana died in 1997 Christmas cards signed by her sold for £3,000 each: now you'd be lucky to get £300-£400. I wouldn't buy anything linked to Diana: Kate has replaced her." However, Diana's dresses can sell for over £100,000 particularly if they are linked to a particular event.
